comments.body:
We don't use the `n>0` elsewhere because it is redundant:

```
src/test/util_tests.cpp:    BOOST_CHECK(!ParseMoney("-1", ret));
```

Also, the syntax is preferable:

``` cpp
if(fail)
  return;
doStuff();
```

vs

``` cpp
if(!fail)
  doStuff();
else
  return;
```
